2025-08-04 09:17:51.498032 | controller | Possible reasons for having these kinds of units are:
2025-08-04 09:17:51.498036 | controller | • A unit may be statically enabled by being symlinked from another unit's
2025-08-04 09:17:51.498040 | controller |   .wants/, .requires/, or .upholds/ directory.
2025-08-04 09:17:51.498043 | controller | • A unit's purpose may be to act as a helper for some other unit which has
2025-08-04 09:17:51.498046 | controller |   a requirement dependency on it.
2025-08-04 09:17:51.498051 | controller | • A unit may be started when needed via activation (socket, path, timer,
2025-08-04 09:17:51.498059 | controller |   D-Bus, udev, scripted systemctl call, ...).
2025-08-04 09:17:51.498063 | controller | • In case of template units, the unit is meant to be enabled with some
2025-08-04 09:17:51.498066 | controller |   instance name specified.
